, Total Time: 1 hrs, Servings: 6','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/ptDXctfp5NjeM-gEfBVU5FNGrGs=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/7122690-ded28351dcdd4eedb0d36c70a0463ae7.jpg'),(149,'Oliebollen (Dutch Doughnuts)','20 mins','10 mins','1 hrs 35 mins',12,'1 dozen','1 (0.6 ounce) cake compressed fresh yeast, 1 cup lukewarm milk, 2 Â¼ cups all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons salt, 1 large egg, Â¾ cup dried currants, Â¾ cup raisins, 1 medium Granny Smith apple - peeled, cored and finely chopped, 1 quart vegetable oil for deep-frying, 1 cup confectioners\' sugar for dusting','Break up compressed yeast and stir into warm milk. Let stand for a few minutes to dissolve.\nSift flour and salt into a large bowl. Stir in yeast mixture and egg until smooth. Stir in currants, raisins, and apple. Cover the bowl and set in a warm place to rise until doubled in volume, about 1 hour.\nHeat oil in a deep-fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).\nUse two metal spoons to shape scoops of dough into 12 balls. Drop them carefully into the hot oil and fry until golden brown, about 8 minutes. Remove doughnuts with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.\nDust doughnuts with confectioners\' sugar. Transfer to a serving platter and dust with more confectioners\' sugar.',4.3,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/46299/oliebollen-dutch-doughnuts/','/Bread/Pastries/Doughnuts/','Total Fat 9g 11%, Saturated Fat 1g 7%, Cholesterol 17mg 6%, Sodium 405mg 18%, Total Carbohydrate 46g 17%, Dietary Fiber 2g 7%, Total Sugars 25g, Protein 5g, Vitamin C 1mg 7%, Calcium 44mg 3%, Iron 2mg 9%, Potassium 240mg 5%','Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 10 mins, Additional Time: 1 hrs 5 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 35 mins, Servings: 12, Yield: 1 dozen','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/z0hOkzWARH8A5EcKtAvFE_5QppY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/3062572-oliebollen-dutch-doughnuts-Venessa-Benlolo-4x3-1-0870006cb16349e0984cb636d71a4899.jpg'),(150,'Classic Cherries Jubilee','10 mins','20 mins','30 mins',6,'','Â½ cup white sugar, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, Â¼ cup cold water, Â¼ cup orange juice, 1 pound Bing or other dark, sweet cherries, rinsed and pitted (or use frozen pitted cherries), Â½ teaspoon finely grated orange zest, 3 cups vanilla bean ice cream, Â¼ teaspoon cherry extract, Â¼ cup brandy','Whisk sugar and cornstarch together in a wide saucepan. Stir in water and orange juice; bring to a boil over medium-high heat, whisking until thickened. Stir in cherries and orange zest; return to a boil, then reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes. While cherries are cooking, spoon ice cream into serving bowls.\nRemove cherries from heat and stir in cherry extract. Pour in brandy and ignite with a long lighter. Gently shake the pan until blue flame has extinguished itself. Spoon cherries over ice cream.',4.7,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/74422/classic-cherries-jubilee/','/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Cherry Dessert Recipes/','Total Fat 8g 10%, Saturated Fat 5g 23%, Cholesterol 29mg 10%, Sodium 54mg 2%, Total Carbohydrate 48g 18%, Dietary Fiber 2g 8%, Total Sugars 42g, Protein 3g, Vitamin C 11mg 56%, Calcium 98mg 8%, Iron 0mg 2%, Potassium 323mg 7%','Prep Time: 10 mins, Cook Time: 20 mins, Total Time: 30 mins, Servings: 6','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Zm7vM-30Ts_k-DUqdXdBj103GYU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/74422-classic-cherries-jubilee-ddmfs-4x3-1-feb1560d0011415c99e921a16ebe89f1.jpg'),(151,'Fresh Cherry Cobbler','1 hrs','1 hrs','2 hrs',12,'','Â½ cup butter, 1 cup all-purpose flour, 1 Â¾ cups white sugar, divided, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 cup milk, 2 cups pitted sour cherries, 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place butter in a 9x13-inch baking dish, and place in the oven to melt while the oven is preheating. Remove as soon as butter has melted, about 5 minutes.\nStir together 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, and baking powder in a medium bowl. Mix in milk until well blended, then pour the batter into the pan over the melted butter. Do not stir.\nRinse out the bowl from the batter, and dry. Place cherries into the bowl, and toss with remaining 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour. Distribute the cherry mixture evenly over the batter. Do not stir.\nBake in the preheated oven until golden brown, 50 to 60 minutes. A toothpick inserted into the cobber should come out clean.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAllrecipes Magazine\n',4.3,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/72815/fresh-cherry-cobbler/','/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Cherry Dessert Recipes/','Total Fat 8g 11%, Saturated Fat 5g 26%, Cholesterol 22mg 7%, Sodium 94mg 4%, Total Carbohydrate 42g 15%, Dietary Fiber 1g 3%, Total Sugars 32g, Protein 2g, Vitamin C 3mg 13%, Calcium 49mg 4%, Iron 1mg 3%, Potassium 90mg 2%','Prep Time: 1 hrs, Cook Time: 1 hrs, Total Time: 2 hrs, Servings: 12','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/7Chv6g13eQlvJA6bf1zsv3nzniU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2466557-fresh-cherry-cobbler-Allrecipes-Magazine-1x1-1-9a2810e60cbb4673915d8da83eac897b.jpg'),(152,'Cherry Pie Filling','25 mins','15 mins','40 mins',6,'4 cups','4 cups pitted tart red cherries, 1 cup white sugar, Â¼ cup cornstarch','Place cherries into a saucepan over medium heat. Cover and cook, stirring often, until cherries release their juices and come to a simmer, 10 to 15 minutes.\nWhisk sugar with cornstarch in a bowl until combined; pour mixture into hot cherries and juice. Stir until thoroughly combined.\nBring to a simmer over low heat; cook until thickened, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool before using as pie filling.',4.7,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/218432/cherry-pie-filling/','/Desserts/Fillings/Fruit Fillings/','Total Fat 1g 1%, Saturated Fat 0g 1%, Sodium 1mg 0%, Total Carbohydrate 54g 20%, Dietary Fiber 2g 8%, Total Sugars 47g, Protein 1g, Vitamin C 7mg 34%, Calcium 15mg 1%, Iron 0mg 2%, Potassium 217mg 5%','Prep Time: 25 mins, Cook Time: 15 mins, Total Time: 40 