g bowl. Pour enough milk into the reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup of liquid; add to cake and pudding mixture. Pour in vegetable oil. Mix on low speed, adding 1 egg at a time, until blended. Increase speed to medium; mix until thoroughly combined and smooth, about 2 minutes. Pour batter over pineapples and cherries in the pan.\nBake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan.',4.9,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/272616/pineapple-upside-down-bundt-cake/','/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Cherry Dessert Recipes/','Total Fat 20g 26%, Saturated Fat 7g 34%, Cholesterol 63mg 21%, Sodium 477mg 21%, Total Carbohydrate 57g 21%, Dietary Fiber 1g 3%, Total Sugars 37g, Protein 4g, Vitamin C 2mg 10%, Calcium 82mg 6%, Iron 1mg 6%, Potassium 85mg 2%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 35 mins, Additional Time: 10 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 15 mins, Servings: 12, Yield: 1 10-inch bundt cake','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/srekPtZAvSl0NfhyhARMaXbXALk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Pineapple-Upside-Down-Bundt-Cake-2000-ece59af0172b423182e18f5ce21a0b27.jpeg'),(156,'Grandma\'s Skillet Pineapple Upside-Down Cake','15 mins','45 mins','1 hrs 10 mins',12,'1 cake','1 stick butter, 1 Â½ cups packed brown sugar, 1 (20 ounce) can sliced pineapple, 1 (4 ounce) jar cherries, 1 Â½ cups all-purpose flour, 2 Â½ teaspoons baking powder, Â½ teaspoon salt, 1 Â½ cups white sugar, Â½ cup butter, 2 large eggs, 1 cup milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla extract','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).\nMelt 1 stick butter in the bottom of a cast iron skillet over medium heat, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter. Add pineapple slices to the skillet in a decorative layer with a cherry in the middle of each pineapple ring. Set aside.\nSift flour, baking powder, and salt together in a bowl.\nCream sugar and 1/2 cup butter together in 