g pan. Roast in the preheated oven to desired doneness. For medium-rare, a thermometer inserted into the center will read 140 degrees F (60 degrees C). Remove lamb from the oven and cover with foil. Allow to rest for 15 minutes while proceeding with the recipe.\nWhile the lamb is resting, bring the balsamic vinegar to a boil in a small saucepan over high heat. Boil until the vinegar has reduced by half, 4 to 5 minutes. Once reduced, stir in the butter, honey, and sliced figs. Stir until the butter has melted, then remove from the heat, stir in the chopped basil and set aside.\nTo serve, remove the twine from the lamb and cut into 1/2 inch thick slices. Arrange on a warm serving platter and drizzle with the fig sauce, garnish with mint and basil leaves.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n',4.8,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/112260/stuffed-leg-of-lamb-with-balsamic-fig-basil-sauce/','/Meat and Poultry/Lamb/Leg/','Total Fat 40g 51%, Saturated Fat 15g 76%, Cholesterol 147mg 49%, Sodium 649mg 28%, Total Carbohydrate 29g 11%, Dietary Fiber 3g 11%, Total Sugars 23g, Protein 38g, Vitamin C 5mg 25%, Calcium 86mg 7%, Iron 4mg 21%, Potassium 691mg 15%','Prep Time: 50 mins, Cook Time: 1 hrs, Additional Time: 10 mins, Total Time: 2 hrs, Servings: 6, Yield: 1 lamb roast','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Ldbc-dwMKsu_egoSmhOIGlvNNcI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/601260-696275d25a7e45cab54defc0b25fd76d.jpg'),(223,'Bourbon Fig Compote','10 mins','30 mins','40 mins',12,'12 servings','7 ounces dried Mission figs, diced, Â¼ cup white sugar, Â¼ cup bourbon whiskey, Â¼ cup balsamic vinegar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 pinch salt','Combine figs, sugar, whiskey, balsamic vinegar, lemon juice, and salt in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until liquid reduces by half, about 30 minutes. Cool before serving.',4.8,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/232620/bourbon-fig-compote/','/Appetizers and Snacks/Dips and Spreads Recipes/','Total Fat 0g 0%, Sodium 3m