anulated sugar, or as needed (Optional), Â½ cup dark chocolate chips (Optional)','Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\nStir apple, pear, brown sugar, vanilla extract, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and salt together in a bowl. Whisk egg and water together in a small bowl.\nRoll pastry out on a lightly floured surface; cut into circles with a 3- to 4-inch round cookie cutter. Spoon a small amount of apple mixture onto center of each pastry circle; fold circles in half and press firmly to seal edges. Crimp with a fork, if desired. Place pies on prepared baking sheet.\nCut 3 small slits in top of each hand pie with a sharp knife. Brush surface of pies with egg mixture; sprinkle with decorating sugar.\nBake in the preheated oven until lightly golden, about 25 minutes; allow pies to cool to room temperature, about 20 minutes.\nMelt chocolate chips in a microwave-safe glass or ceramic bowl in 15-second intervals, stirring after each melting, 1 to 2 minutes. Drizzle melted chocolate over pies.',4,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/244986/autumn-spiced-apple-and-pear-hand-pies/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 6g 7%, Saturated Fat 2g 10%, Cholesterol 12mg 4%, Sodium 75mg 3%, Total Carbohydrate 18g 7%, Dietary Fiber 1g 5%, Total Sugars 8g, Protein 2g, Vitamin C 1mg 6%, Calcium 11mg 1%, Iron 1mg 3%, Potassium 64mg 1%','Prep Time: 1 hrs, Cook Time: 30 mins, Additional Time: 20 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 50 mins, Servings: 16, Yield: 16 3-inch pies','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/1D71LVaZANfmtHoKdbMS08_K1KE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4138565-8da5900b557e4b87b4fa5031027914fd.jpg'),(414,'Pear Pie','15 mins','45 mins','1 hrs',8,'1 9-inch pie','1 (9 inch) unbaked pie crust, 3 cups sliced Bartlett pears, 1 cup sour cream, Â½ cup white sugar, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, 1  egg, Â½ teaspoon vanilla extract, Â½ teaspoon salt','Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Press pie crust into a 9-inch pie dish.\nArrange pear slices in the pie crust. Stir sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, egg, vanilla extract, and salt together in a bowl; pour over pears.\nMix 1/2 cup flour, butter, 1/4 cup sugar, and cinnamon together in a bowl until topping resembles coarse crumbs.\nBake pie in the preheated oven for 35 minutes. Sprinkle topping onto pie and continue baking until topping is golden brown, about 10 more minutes.',4.8,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/234491/pear-pie/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 26g 33%, Saturated Fat 13g 66%, Cholesterol 66mg 22%, Sodium 369mg 16%, Total Carbohydrate 48g 17%, Dietary Fiber 3g 11%, Total Sugars 25g, Protein 5g, Vitamin C 3mg 15%, Calcium 53mg 4%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 154mg 3%','Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 45 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 9-inch pie','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/1OpC8i9pAKJWprNyb2R8tJHEAZk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2597871-b7015a586c8346e0b291a65bf336549a.jpg'),(415,'Pear Pie II','15 mins','50 mins','1 hrs 5 mins',6,'1 to 9 - inch pie','1 (9 inch) unbaked pie crust, 3  eggs, â…“ cup all-purpose flour, 1 cup white sugar, 1 teaspoon almond extract, Â¼ cup melted butter, 3  pears - peeled, cored and sliced','Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C.)\nIn a large bowl, combine eggs, flour, sugar, almond extract and melted butter. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Arrange sliced pears in spokes radiating from center.\nBake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and bake for 25 to 35 minutes, or until custard is firm. Cool completely before serving.',4.4,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/23767/pear-pie-ii/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 20g 26%, Saturated Fat 8g 41%, Cholesterol 113mg 38%, Sodium 247mg 11%, Total Carbohydrate 69g 25%, Dietary Fiber 5g 16%, Total Sugars 44g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 4mg 22%, Calcium 29mg 2%, Iron 2mg 10%, Potassium 187mg 4%','Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 50 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 5 mins, Servings: 6, Yield: 1 to 9 - inch pie','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Pn5zAQLFhmsLBZBwh_9AW3JqsG4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/481241-bdc084e3cab54ba18a80ae802608d015.jpg'),(416,'Pear and Hazelnut Frangipane Tart','15 mins','50 mins','2 hrs 15 mins',8,'1 9-inch tart','1 Â¼ cups all-purpose flour (or gluten-free flour mix), 1 teaspoon sugar, Â¼ teaspoon salt, 8 tablespoons cold unsalted butter, cut into 1/2-inch cubes, 3 tablespoons cold water, or more as needed ,   ReynoldsÂ® Parchment Paper,   Reynolds WrapÂ® Aluminum Foil','Combine the flour, sugar and salt in a food processor. Add the cold butter and pulse ten times until the butter is the size of large peas. Add 3 tablespoons of cold water and pulse until it comes together. Turn onto a lightly floured work surface and bring the dough together, forming a disk. Wrap in ReynoldsÂ® Parchment Paper and refrigerate for at least 45 minutes.\nOn a lightly floured work surface, roll the dough to 1/8-inch thickness. Fill a 9-inch tart mold or rectangle tart mold with the dough. Cut off excess from the top and refrigerate for another 15 minutes.\nPreheat oven to 400 degrees F. Cover the top of the dough with Reynolds WrapÂ® Aluminum Foil and weigh down with pie weights or dry beans. Bake for 15 minutes. Remove the foil and pie weights and let cool.\nCombine the hazelnuts and sugar in the food processor. Pulse to a fine powder. Add the butter, egg, flour, vanilla, rum and salt. Process until it comes together as a paste.\nSpread the mixture over the partially baked tart. On the top, arrange the pear slices in a pattern. Bake the tart for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown. Let it cool for 10 minutes before slicing.',5,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/245237/pear-and-hazelnut-frangipane-tart/','/Desserts/','Total Fat 31g 39%, Saturated Fat 15g 77%, Cholesterol 84mg 28%, Sodium 206mg 9%, Total Carbohydrate 46g 17%, Dietary Fiber 4g 13%, Total Sugars 20g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 3mg 17%, Calcium 33mg 3%, Iron 2mg 11%, Potassium 194mg 4%','Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 50 mins, Additional Time: 1 hrs 10 mins, Total Time: 2 hrs 15 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 9-inch tart','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/DdP5RZO0aDVvbe073M4PWRdswbI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2822093-8810754f3fcb40419f3fd01d5fe5f4f2.jpg'),(417,'French Puff Pastry Tart with Pears and Chocolate','20 mins','30 mins','50 mins',8,'8 servings','Â½ cup unsalted butter, Â½ cup white sugar, 2 tablespoons white sugar, 1 cup blanched almond flour, 2  eggs, 1 sheet frozen puff pastry, thawed, 4 ounces milk chocolate, chopped, 3  pears - peeled, cored and sliced','Line a tart pan with parchment paper. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).\nCombine butter and 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar in a large bowl; beat using an electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Mix in almond flour. Add eggs 1 at a time and mix until well combined.\nLine a tart pan with the puff pastry and prick with a fork all over.\nPlace chocolate in the top of a double boiler over simmering water. Stir frequently, scraping down the sides with a rubber spatula to avoid scorching, until melted, about 5 minutes. Cool slightly. Cover puff pastry with melted chocolate.\nCarefully pour egg mixture on top of the chocolate on the puff pastry without mixing the 2 layers. Arrange pear slices on top of the tart.\nBake in the preheated oven until pastry has puffed up and is golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.',5,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/267990/french-puff-pastry-tart-with-pears-and-chocolate/','/Cuisine/European/French/','Total Fat 36g 46%, Saturated Fat 14g 68%, Cholesterol 80mg 27%, Sodium 106mg 5%, Total Carbohydrate 51g 18%, Dietary Fiber 5g 16%, Total Sugars 30g, Protein 9g, Vitamin C 3mg 13%, Calcium 45mg 3%, Iron 1mg 8%, Potassium 165mg 4%','Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 30 mins, Total Time: 50 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 8 servings','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/6rxJJd52wxPxR7w8RdjCC6dB_8w=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/5772017-a6f82629aff24d2e9508bd41062da5e9.jpg'),(418,'Frangipane Pear Tart','30 mins','1 hrs 15 mins','2 hrs 15 mins',8,'1 9-inch tart','4 cups water, 1 cup white sugar, 2 tablespoons honey, 1  vanilla bean, split lengthwise, 1  cinnamon stick, 5 pods cardamom, crushed, 4  Conference pears - peeled, halved, and cored','Combine water, 1 cup white sugar, honey, vanilla bean, cinnamon stick, and cardamom in a large saucepan. Bring to a simmer over medium heat. Add pears; reduce heat and simmer until pears are translucent or easily pierced with a knife, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.\nCombine 1 1/2 cup flour, confectioners\' sugar, and salt in a bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup plus 1 tablespoon butter until mixture is crumbly. Mix in egg yolk until dough sticks together in large clumps.\nGrease a 9-inch tart pan with a removable bottom. Press dough evenly into the pan. Freeze for 30 minutes. Reserve leftover dough for patching cracks.\nPreheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).\nGrease the shiny side of a piece of aluminum foil with butter; place butter-side down over the pastry. Transfer tart pan to a baking sheet.\nBake in the preheated oven, using leftover dough to patch any cracks, until dough looks dry and light brown, about 20 minutes. Peel off aluminum foil; let pastry cool.\nReduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\nCombine 2/3 cup white sugar and 1/3 cup butter in a large bowl; beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Mix in ground almonds. Add egg, egg yolk, 2 teaspoons flour, and cornstarch; beat until frangipane is smooth. Beat in almond extract and vanilla extract.\nSpread frangipane evenly over the pastry. Drain pear halves and dry with paper towels. Cut lengthwise into even slices. Place 1 pear half on a spatula and gently fan out slices. Place on frangipane. Repeat with remaining pear halves.\nBake in the preheated oven until frangipane is firm to the touch, 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.',4.7,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/256822/frangipane-pear-tart/','/Desserts/Pies/Tarts/Fruit Tart Recipes/','Total Fat 24g 31%, Saturated Fat 14g 69%, Cholesterol 104mg 35%, Sodium 171mg 7%, Total Carbohydrate 94g 34%, Dietary Fiber 4g 15%, Total Sugars 66g, Protein 9g, Vitamin C 5mg 23%, Calcium 79mg 6%, Iron 2mg 13%, Potassium 330mg 7%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 1 hrs 15 mins, Additional Time: 30 mins, Total Time: 2 hrs 15 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 9-inch tart','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/0RYtZ6H3YjGnxC3-naUAHG6zcSo=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/6332333-354566c466c3473b8cc2b46fbf1e18de.jpg'),(419,'d\'Anjou Pear and Almond Tarts','15 mins','45 mins','1 hrs',18,'18 3-inch tarts','18 (3 inch) unbaked tart shells, 7 tablespoons brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter, melted, 1 teaspoon pear-flavored white balsamic vinegar, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, 3 large ripe d\'Anjou pears - peeled, cored, and diced, 3 tablespoons chopped almonds','Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place tart shells on a baking sheet.\nStir brown sugar, melted butter, balsamic vinegar, and cinnamon together in a bowl; stir in pears and chopped almonds until completely coated. Spoon pear mixture into tart shells.\nBake in the preheated oven until golden, about 45 minutes.',5,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/241123/danjou-pear-and-almond-tarts/','/Desserts/Pies/Tarts/Fruit Tart Recipes/','Total Fat 8g 11%, Saturated Fat 2g 12%, Cholesterol 4mg 1%, Sodium 101mg 4%, Total Carbohydrate 30g 11%, Dietary Fiber 1g 5%, Total Sugars 14g, Protein 2g, Vitamin C 2mg 8%, Calcium 14mg 1%, Iron 1mg 4%, Potassium 57mg 1%','Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 45 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs, Servings: 18, Yield: 18 3-inch tarts','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/N-uoNEWcjOsrH-y2omC2Q4lRWu0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2144568-f4c929cac211468bae2bbe3865ebf6ba.jpg'),(420,'Creamy Pear Pie','20 mins','55 mins','1 hrs 15 mins',8,'1 to 9 - inch pie','â…“ cup white sugar, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, 4 cups peeled and sliced pears, 1 cup sour cream, Â½ teaspoon vanilla extract, Â½ teaspoon lemon extract, Â½ teaspoon almond extract, 1 (9 inch) unbaked pie shell','Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).\nIn a large bowl, stir together the white sugar and 2 tablespoons flour. Add pears, and toss to coat. Stir in the sour cream and vanilla, lemon and almond extracts until the pears are evenly coated. Pour into the unbaked pie shell.\nIn a small bowl, mix together 1/4 cup flour and brown sugar. Mix in the butter with your fingers until the mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over the top of the pie.\nBake for 10 minutes in the preheated oven, then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Bake for an additional 45 minutes, or until pears are tender.',4.4,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/47915/creamy-pear-pie/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 17g 21%, Saturated Fat 7g 37%, Cholesterol 20mg 7%, Sodium 155mg 7%, Total Carbohydrate 40g 15%, Dietary Fiber 4g 13%, Total Sugars 20g, Protein 3g, Vitamin C 4mg 19%, Calcium 48mg 4%, Iron 1mg 6%, Potassium 166mg 4%','Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 55 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 15 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 to 9 - inch pie','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/DXLdk0i5ifjWVGo5B6hAFI7o0QY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/1088180-353550eaa56043299622e8d6c453efce.jpg'),(421,'Jump Rope Pie','30 mins','50 mins','1 hrs 20 mins',8,'1 9-inch pie','1 recipe pastry for a double crust 9-inch pie, 1 cup white sugar, 3 tablespoons all-purpose flour, or more as needed, Â½ teaspoon ground cinnamon, 1 pinch freshly grated nutmeg, 2 cups peeled, cored and sliced apples, 1 cup peeled, pitted and sliced peaches, 1 cup peeled, cored and sliced pears, 1 cup pitted and sliced plums, 1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger root, 1 tablespoon lemon juice','Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.\nWhisk sugar, flour, cinnamon, and nutmeg together in a small bowl; sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar mixture over pastry in pie plate.\nStir apples, peaches, pears, plums, and ginger together in a bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice and stir to distribute. Place fruit mixture in pie plate; sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture. Cover with pastry, pinch to seal top and bottom crusts together, and cut a few slits in top pastry with a sharp knife. Alternatively, cover with a lattice crust.\nBake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) and continue baking until crust is golden and filling has thickened, about 35 minutes. Cool completely before serving.',3.8,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/245114/jump-rope-pie/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 15g 19%, Saturated Fat 4g 19%, Sodium 235mg 10%, Total Carbohydrate 58g 21%, Dietary Fiber 3g 12%, Total Sugars 33g, Protein 3g, Vitamin C 12mg 59%, Calcium 14mg 1%, Iron 2mg 8%, Potassium 128mg 3%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 50 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 20 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 9-inch pie','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/I2qSvHBzdYKRBGAcfawfYd5Bq70=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2636699-be14b06a97ea47ae938245bb3788d70c.jpg'),(422,'Dethbert\'s Pear Pie','30 mins','25 mins','55 mins',16,'2 pies','1 cup all-purpose flour, Â½ cup white sugar, Â½ teaspoon salt, 2 cups finely shredded mild Cheddar cheese, 1 cup butter, softened','Sift flour, sugar, and salt into a mixing bowl. Stir grated Cheddar cheese into the flour mixture using a fork. Stir in butter using a wide spoon until mixture becomes crumbly. Set topping mixture aside at room temperature.\nPreheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Place pie crusts in their tins onto a baking sheet to catch drips; place crusts 1 inch apart.\nSift sugar, cornstarch, and salt into a small bowl. Place pears in a large mixing bowl. When oven is hot, sprinkle sugar mixture over pears and stir to combine. Pour filling evenly into the 2 pie crusts. Divide topping mixture in half and add to the top of each pie in 4 to 6 dollops; use a wide knife to spread evenly.\nBake on the middle rack of the preheated oven for about 18 minutes; the pears will produce a lot of liquid and will bubble over. Check pies and cover with aluminum foil if crust or topping is getting dark. Bake about 7 minutes more.',2,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/268820/dethberts-pear-pie/','/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Pear Pie Recipes/','Total Fat 24g 31%, Saturated Fat 12g 61%, Cholesterol 45mg 15%, Sodium 397mg 17%, Total Carbohydrate 52g 19%, Dietary Fiber 5g 18%, Total Sugars 28g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 6mg 28%, Calcium 121mg 9%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 196mg 4%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 25 mins, Total Time: 55 mins, Servings: 16, Yield: 2 pies','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/aCnCUfJ4QNBHOM2m6j2t_laqRRk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/5968966-380a9ef7811649779e96fbbbd8e2d8a1.jpg'),(423,'Coffee-Dusted Pear Galette','30 mins','20 mins','50 mins',4,'4 servings','1 Â½ cups all-purpose flour, 1 Â½ teaspoons white granulated sugar, 1 teaspoon fine sea salt, Â½ cup unsalted butter, frozen, 7 tablespoons ice-cold water, or more as needed, divided, 1 large egg, beaten (for egg wash), 1 tablespoon turbinado sugar, 1 sheet Reynolds WrapÂ® Aluminum Foil, 1 sheet ReynoldsÂ® Parchment Paper','In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar and salt. Using a box grater, grate the cold butter atop the flour mixture. Working quickly and using your hands, break the butter bits into the flour until they\'re evenly distributed and resemble the size of small peas.\nAdd 4 tablespoons of water and mix. The mixture will be shaggy at this point. From here, add 1 tablespoon of water at a time until the dough comes together (generally about 3 additional tablespoons). Flour a work surface and dump the dough onto it. Knead a few times until it comes together. Form dough into a disk. Wrap the disk in plastic wrap and transfer to the refrigerator to chill for at least 1 hour, ideally overnight.\nJust before the dough is ready to remove from the fridge, mix together the filling. In a medium bowl, toss together the pear slices, brown sugar, cocoa powder, coffee grounds, vanilla extract and salt.\nRemove the disk of dough from the refrigerator and allow to come to room temperature for 10 minutes. Liberally flour a work surface and rolling pin. Begin to roll the dough to a 16-inch round, being sure to rotate it every so often to avoid sticking, Using the bottom of a bowl or plate that measures about 6 inches in diameter, cut out 3 circles. Re-roll the scraps to get 1 additional circle.\nArrange the pears slices neatly in a circular pattern in the center of each of the pie crust rounds, leaving about 1 1/2 inch clear at the edges. Fold over the edges to cover about 1/2 inch of the filling. Repeat with the remaining rounds. Transfer the galettes to a baking sheet lined with ReynoldsÂ® Parchment Paper and place in the freezer to chill for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat your oven to 400 degrees F.\nLastly, brush the pie crust edges with the egg wash and sprinkle with turbinado sugar. Transfer to the oven to bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until the edges are golden brown. Check on the galettes periodically. If at any time the crusts\' edges are getting too brown, take a piece of Reynolds WrapÂ® Aluminum Foil and tent over the edges. When the edges are golden brown, remove from the oven. Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream or a scoop of your favorite vanilla ice cream.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n',2,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/244894/coffee-dusted-pear-galette/','/Desserts/','Total Fat 25g 32%, Saturated Fat 15g 76%, Cholesterol 108mg 36%, Sodium 509mg 22%, Total Carbohydrate 67g 24%, Dietary Fiber 4g 14%, Total Sugars 26g, Protein 7g, Vitamin C 4mg 18%, Calcium 45mg 3%, Iron 8mg 44%, Potassium 235mg 5%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 20 mins, Total Time: 50 mins, Servings: 4, Yield: 4 servings','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/xGjsNF6obs4hgzQghG_11Hfm06Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2579527-072fd83e897a405ba6e1a038163d5b3f.jpg'),(424,'Grandma\'s Pear Preserves','30 mins','15 mins','12 hrs 45 mins',48,'6 half pints','6 cups peeled, cored, and sliced pears, 1 cup water, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 (2 ounce) package powdered fruit pectin, 8 cups white sugar, Â½ cup brown sugar, 2 teaspoons ground allspice, 2 teaspoons ground nutmeg','Inspect six 8-ounce jars for cracks and rings for rust, discarding any defective ones. Immerse in simmering water for 10 minutes. Wash new, unused lids and rings in warm, soapy water.\nMeanwhile, combine pears, water, and lemon juice in a large saucepan. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in pectin, and bring to a full boil. Stir in white sugar; boil and stir until sugar is dissolved, about 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar, allspice, and nutmeg.\nPack pear preserves into hot, sterilized jars, filling to within 1/2 inch of the top. Run a clean knife or thin spatula around the insides of the jars to remove any air bubbles. Wipe rims with a moist paper towel to remove any residue. Top with lids and screw rings on tightly.\nPlace a rack in the bottom of a large stockpot and fill halfway with water. Bring to a boil and lower jars 2 inches apart into the boiling water using a holder. Pour in more boiling water to cover jars by at least 1 inch. Bring to a rolling boil, cover, and process for 10 minutes.\nRemove the jars from the stockpot and let rest, several inches apart, for 12 to 24 hours. Press the center of each lid with a finger to ensure the lid does not move up or down. Remove the rings for storage and store in a cool, dark area.',3.9,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/53839/grandmas-pear-preserves/','/Side Dish/Sauces and Condiments/Canning and Preserving Recipes/Jams and Jellies Recipes/','Total Fat 0g 0%, Sodium 1mg 0%, Total Carbohydrate 39g 14%, Dietary Fiber 1g 3%, Total Sugars 38g, Protein 0g, Vitamin C 1mg 5%, Calcium 5mg 0%, Iron 0mg 1%, Potassium 30mg 1%','Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 15 mins, Additional Time: 12 hrs, Total Time: 12 hrs 45 mins, Servings: 48, Yield: 6 half pints','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/AXuEicwlKL10iCW-FZ91zP2K_yg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/9411412-grandmas-pear-preserves-Trusted-Brands-4x3-1-64526ec51bd240bf911ed95f10e6f63e.jpg'),(425,'Pear Jam','20 mins','20 mins','40 mins',64,'8 half-pint jars','4 Â½ cups mashed ripe pears, Â¼ cup lemon juice, 3 tablespoons powdered fruit pectin, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, Â½ teaspoon ground cloves, Â½ teaspoon ground allspice, Â½ teaspoon ground nutmeg, 7 Â½ cups white sugar, 1 teaspoon butter, 8  half-pint canning jars with lids and rings, or as needed','Mix pears, lemon juice, fruit pectin, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, and nutmeg in a large heavy pot; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add sugar all at once, stirring, and bring back to a full rolling boil. Boil for 1 minute. Mix in butter to settle foam.\nSterilize the jars and lids in boiling water for at least 5 minutes. Pack the pear jam into the hot, sterilized jars, filling the jars to within 1/4 inch of the top. Run a knife or a thin spatula around the insides of the jars after they have been filled to remove any air bubbles. Wipe the rims of the jars with a moist paper towel to remove any food residue. Top with lids, and screw-on rings.\nPlace a rack in the bottom of a large stockpot and fill halfway with water. Bring to a boil and lower jars into the boiling water using a holder. Leave a 2-inch space between the jars. Pour in more boiling water if necessary to bring the water level to at least 1 inch above the tops of the jars. Bring the water to a rolling boil, cover the pot, and process for 10 minutes.\nRemove the jars from the stockpot and place onto a cloth-covered or wood surface, several inches apart, until cool. Once cool, press the top of each lid with a finger, ensuring that the seal is tight (lid does not move up or down at all). Store in a cool, dark area.',4.4,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/228625/pear-jam/','/Side Dish/Sauces and Condiments/Canning and Preserving Recipes/Jams and Jellies Recipes/','Total Fat 0g 0%, Cholesterol 0mg 0%, Sodium 1mg 0%, Total Carbohydrate 25g 9%, Dietary Fiber 0g 1%, Total Sugars 25g, Protein 0g, Vitamin C 1mg 5%, Calcium 2mg 0%, Potassium 16mg 0%','Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 20 mins, Total Time: 40 mins, Servings: 64, Yield: 8 half-pint jars','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/YS1Dg6RJq4f2398UDZWkz65qUqM=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4554157-1d1a6c2cba9945f38442a7cc0312904b.jpg'),(426,'Apple and Pear Crumble','20 mins','40 mins','1 hrs',8,'','1 Â½ cups rolled oats, 1 Â½ cups brown sugar, divided, Â½ cup all-purpose flour, Â½ cup butter, softened, 2 cups peeled and diced apples, 2 cups peeled and diced pears, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, Â½ cup sliced almonds, or to taste','Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\nMix oats, 3/4 cup brown sugar, flour, and butter together in a bowl until crumbly.\nMix apples, pears, remaining 3/4 cup brown sugar, and cinnamon together in a separate bowl; spread into the bottom of a 9x9-inch glass pan. Sprinkle oat mixture atop apple-pear mixture; top with almonds.\nBake in the preheated oven until the top is golden brown, about 40 minutes.',4.5,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/229252/apple-and-pear-crumble/','/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Apple Dessert Recipes/','Total Fat 16g 20%, Saturated Fat 8g 39%, Cholesterol 31mg 10%, Sodium 91mg 4%, Total Carbohydrate 55g 20%, Dietary Fiber 5g 16%, Total Sugars 34g, Protein 5g, Vitamin C 3mg 16%, Calcium 58mg 4%, Iron 2mg 9%, Potassium 230mg 5%