gar and let stand for one hour.\nPreheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray a 10 inch bundt pan with non-stick cooking spray.\nSlightly beat the egg whites and combine them with the oil, chopped pecans and pear mixture.\nStir the flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in the pear mixture. Pour batter into the prepared bundt pan.\nBake at 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from oven ant let cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before removing form pan.',4.6,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/8212/fresh-pear-cake/','/Desserts/Cakes/Spice Cake Recipes/','Total Fat 20g 25%, Saturated Fat 2g 8%, Sodium 371mg 16%, Total Carbohydrate 67g 24%, Dietary Fiber 4g 13%, Total Sugars 39g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 3mg 13%, Calcium 20mg 2%, Iron 2mg 10%, Potassium 158mg 3%','Servings: 12, Yield: 1 to 10 - inch bundt cake','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/7to9HQBWdH8WgWX38lHu_-ohQ2g=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/7264740-19d31189eee0409a9e5728fcd035ca67.jpg'),(430,'Classic Pear Crisp','20 mins','35 mins','1 hrs',6,'6 servings','1 cup rolled oats, â…“ cup brown sugar, Â½ cup all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon finely chopped crystallized ginger, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, Â¼ cup butter, 2 tablespoons white sugar, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons finely chopped crystallized ginger, 8 cups peeled and sliced pears, 1 pint vanilla ice cream','Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 2 quart casserole dish or 9 inch square baking dish.\nIn a medium bowl, stir together the oats, brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour, 1 teaspoon crystallized ginger, and cinnamon. Stir in the butter until the mixture is crumbly with pea sized lumps. Set aside.\nIn a separate bowl, stir together the white sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 2 teaspoons of crystallized ginger. Add the sliced pears, and toss to blend. Transfer to the prepared baking dish. Spread with the oat topping.\nBake for 30 to 35 minutes in the preheated oven, until pears are soft and topping is golden brown. Cool slightly before serving with vanilla ice cream.',4.2,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/91539/classic-pear-crisp/','/Desserts/Crisps and Crumbles Recipes/Pear Crisps and Crumbles Recipes/','Total Fat 14g 18%, Saturated Fat 8g 40%, Cholesterol 40mg 13%, Sodium 97mg 4%, Total Carbohydrate 81g 29%, Dietary Fiber 9g 32%, Total Sugars 47g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 10mg 50%, Calcium 104mg 8%, Iron 2mg 11%, Potassium 457mg 10%','Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 35 mins, Additional Time: 5 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs, Servings: 6, Yield: 6 servings','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/fvOzjOdtaW0leFTmYFnZq6XfatA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/31083-d8473aeadb20400eb308eade4d852343.jpg'),(431,'Pear or Apple Cobbler','15 mins','45 mins','1 hrs',9,'9 servings','4  pears, cored and cut into 1/2-inch slices, 1 teaspoon lemon juice, â…“ cup maple syrup, 2 tablespoons melted butter','Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).\nToss pears and lemon juice together in a bowl until coated; spread into a 9x9-inch baking dish. Pour maple syrup and 2 tablespoons melted butter over pear mixture; toss to coat.\nMix oats, brown sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter, flour, and cinnamon together in a bowl until crumbly; sprinkle over pear mixture.\nBake in the preheated oven until crust is golden and pears are tender, about 45 minutes.',4.7,'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/233068/pear-or-apple-cobbler/','/Desserts/Cobblers/','Total Fat 14g 17%, Saturated Fat 8g 41%, Cholesterol 34mg 11%, Sodium 100mg 4%, Total Carbohydrate 55g 20%, Dietary Fiber 4g 13%, Total Sugars 38g, Protein 2g, Vitamin C 3mg 17%, Calcium 47mg 4%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 190mg 4%','Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 45 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs, Servings: 9, Yield: 9 servings','https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/6_DriKlvyc1cOW1uZpzwQcOYYIU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/1106661-pear-or-apple-cobbler-kawika74-4x3-1-8d866ec2